{
  "message": "feat(writing/wills): redesign OG/Twitter share images around new illustration asset; minor article copy tweak\n\nReplace the prior row-based layout (illustration on the left, large\nheadline on the right) with a centered square illustration surrounded by\na soft radial glow and overlayed metadata, tuned for the 1200x630 OG /\nTwitter card aspect ratio. Both `opengraph-image.tsx` and\n`twitter-image.tsx` now load a locally-colocated\n`./og-illustration.png` (813 KB) instead of the previous\n`../../../assets/wills_estate_post_illustration.webp`, keeping the asset\nnext to the route so the edge runtime resolves it via `import.meta.url`\nwithout cross-directory traversal.\n\nLayout changes (applied symmetrically to both OG and Twitter image\nroutes):\n\n- Switch outer flex container to a centered layout with fixed\n  520x520 illustration canvas and a radial gradient halo\n  (`rgba(6,182,212,0.28) -> rgba(168,85,247,0.16) -> transparent`)\n  rendered via an absolutely-positioned blurred layer.\n- Re-layer title, subtitle, and byline over a translucent dark panel so\n  they stay legible against the illustration's cooler tones.\n- Tighten horizontal gutter from `padding: 40px 80px` to `marginLeft:\n  48` on the illustration block to keep the text column from being\n  pushed off-card at 1200px width.\n\ncomponents/wills-estate-article.tsx: small copy clarification inside\nthe \"Deliverables\" paragraph \u2014 \"forty-five files organized so...\" ->\n\"roughly forty-five files, one per template the skill carries,\norganized so...\". The previous wording implied a fixed count that could\ndrift as templates are added; the new wording ties the number to the\nskill's template set.",
